<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 2:58PM MDT  by NWS Pocatello</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Blaine,
southeastern Lincoln, northwestern Cassia and Minidoka Counties
through 330 PM MDT...
At 258 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Paul, or near Rupert, moving north at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Burley, Rupert, Heyburn, Paul, Acequia, Kimama and Laidlaw Corrals
Airport.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
